19/06/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Defence Ministry announced plans Monday (June 18th) for a joint military drill involving Bulgaria, Romania and Serbia next week.
The three states sealed an agreement on the exercise during a meeting at NATO Headquarters in Brussels earlier this month.
This first trilateral drill will be aimed at improving interoperability in crisis management and will take place along the Danube.
In other news, Serbian army chief Major General Zdravko Ponos has kicked off a visit to China.
Bilateral military co-operation will dominate the agenda.
(BNR, Tanjug, Makfax - 18/06/07)
